40|$|The {{research}} {{discussed in}} this paper was prompted by the writer’s interest in the roles of England’s small country (“market”) towns. It has two aims: first, to discover {{the extent to which}} the work programmes announced in the British government’s Rural White Paper (RWP 2000) (DETR-MAFF 2000) are recognised by <b>town</b> <b>clerks,</b> and second, to find out what town councils are doing, either on their own, or with others, and to gauge the potential and desire that they have for a greater degree of autonomy. In both cases the data was gathered from an online questionnaire sent to <b>town</b> <b>clerks...</b>|$|R
