50|$|New York {{state law}} {{provides}} for elected <b>Town</b> and County <b>Clerks</b> who have separately defined responsibilities. For example, marriage licenses and dog licenses are issued by <b>town</b> <b>clerks</b> while business certificates and real property deeds are maintained by county clerks. Appointed historians are also required at each level. City clerks may administer elections but, outside cities, county election commissioners head the election apparatus.|$|R
