50|$|Cowbridge Town Hall is {{a public}} {{building}} in the South Wales market town of Cowbridge. It is the meeting place for Cowbridge with Llanblethian Town Council, and also houses the <b>town</b> <b>clerk's</b> office, administrative office, Cowbridge Museum and meeting rooms where public events are held.|$|R
50|$|Greek {{inscriptions}} {{discovered at}} Pergamon include {{the rules of}} the <b>town</b> <b>clerks,</b> the so-called Astynomoi inscription, which has added to understanding of Greek municipal laws and regulations, including how roads were kept in repair, regulations regarding the public and private water supply and lavatories.|$|R
